    "description": "Becton Dickinson India Global Group is actively seeking a talented and motivated Medical Officer to join our dynamic team in Jabalpur. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Becton Dickinson India Global Group:\nBecton Dickinson India Global Group is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Master's degree preferred\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Jabalpur, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Becton Dickinson India Global Group!",
